
Task
Symmetrical point on a plane
Points M and N are symmetrical about the origin.
 
Write a function called oppositePoint that takes the numbers x and y (coordinates of point M) as arguments and returns the coordinates of point N as the string "N (x, y)".
Example:
• function oppositePoint (4, 5) must return "N (-4, -5)";
• the oppositePoint (-4, -5) function must return "N (4, 5)";
• the oppositePoint (-4, 5) function must return "N (4, -5)";
• function oppositePoint (4, -5) must return "N (-4, 5)";
• the oppositePoint (4, 0) function must return "N (-4, 0)";
• the oppositePoint (0, 0) function must return "N (0, 0)".

Solution
function oppositePoint (x, y) {
 return x && y === 0? `N ($ {x}, $ {y})`: `N ($ {- x}, $ {- y})`;
}
